==English==
===Etymology===
Arabic آعبد (abd = servant) + آل (al = 'the'). The article آل often assimmilate with epitheta beginning with 'r' and 's'.

===Proper noun===
'''Abdul'''
#a [[Moslem]] [[given name]]
#Arabic for "servant of the" one of 100 names [[epitheta]] for Allah. By example: Abdullatif. Both the epitethum [[Latif]] = 'the Beautiful' as the whole name [[Abdullatif]] are given to [[Muslim]] man. Women gets only the female form [[Latifa]] of one of [[Allah]]'s epitheta.

It should be followed by another word to form a complete name. If that name is [[Muslim]], the added word would be a word describing [[Allah]].

